lead_paragraph: Denise Karbon won the World Cup season-opening giant slalom, her first victory in four years, and the Olympic champion Julia Mancuso finished second in Sölden, Austria. Karbon tore down the Rettenbach course in a two-run combined time of 2 minutes 23.21 seconds. Mancuso finished in 2:23.54 after a speedy start on her second run to rally from 12th. Kathrin Zettel was third in 2:23.73.
